nted evidence preserved in the MT, LXX, and other ancient sources. This study has major implications for both the study of the book of Joshua and text-historical methodology in general.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 0aIntertextuality in the Bible. 4aJoshua 24. 4aRedaktionskritik. 4aSeptuaginta. 4aTextkritik. 7aRELIGION / Biblical Criticism & Interpretation / Old Testament.2bisacsh  aJoshua 24.  aRedaction criticism.  aSeptuagint.  aTextual criticism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2018 Part 1z978311076248808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2018z978311071955008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishz978311060425208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig. Stud., Jewish Stud.2018 Englishz978311060424508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theology, Relig. Studies, Jewish Studies 2018z9783110603248oZDB-23-DGF0 cEPUBz97831106001170 cprintz978311059811740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311060224140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110602241423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110602241/original  a978-3-11-060424-5  EBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig. Stud., Jewish Stud.2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-060425-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-071955-0  DG Plus eBook-Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-076248-8  DG Plus DeG Package 2018 Part 1b2018  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aP